                               Subject : SHIPS

 Maintenance     The cost to maintain ships, planes, and land units.
    Mobility     How much mobility stuff costs
  Ship-types *!  Description of different types of ships.
 Trade-ships *   How to use trade ships

     assault *   Attack coastal sector from ship
       board *   Board enemy ship
       build *   Build ships, planes, land units, nuclear weapons or bridges
       cargo *   List the commodities on board your ships
  coastwatch *   Check from sectors for nearby ships
        fire *   Fire artillery from sector/ship/unit on sector/ship
    fleetadd     Designate members of a "fleet"
        load *   Load goods, people, etc onto a ship
     lookout *   Check from ships for other ships and/or sector types
        lost *   Report lost items
       ltend     Transfer things between a unit and the ship carrying it
        mine *   Drop sea mines from a ship
     mission *   Assign a mission to a ship/plane/unit
        name     Give a name to a ship
    navigate *   Move ship or fleet around
      payoff     Find out the current payoff of a trade ship
       radar *   Perform radar scan from ship or sector
     retreat     Set retreat conditions/paths for ships or fleets
       sbmap *   Big map of all your worldly knowledge around a ship
       scrap *   Scrap a ship, plane, or land unit
     scuttle *   Destroy a ship, plane, or unit
       sdump     Dump raw ship information
        ship *   Report status of ships
        show *   Characteristics of sectors, units, updates and more
        smap *   Get a map around a ship
       sonar *   Use sonar to look for ships
       sstat *   Report statistics of ship, fleet or ships in a given area
       start     Resume production and repairs
        stop     Stop production and repairs
        tend *   Transfer commodities between ships
     torpedo *   Slip a torpedo to some poor sucker (from a sub or ship)
      unload *   Inverse of load (above)
     upgrade      Update  the  tech  of  a ship/unit/plane to the current tech
                 level
       xdump     Extended dump of everything under the sun

For info on a particular topic, type "info <topic>" where <topic>  is  one  of
the topics listed above.  Topics marked by * are the most important and should
be read by new players.  Topics with unusually long info are marked with a !.

